Monte Carlo code

### PARAMETER DISTRIBUTIONS
# What distributions should the prcing params be from?
# We want 0 leq eta leq 4, 1 leq markup leq 3, 0 leq gamma leq 1
unc_parms <- c(
  # eta
  eta_mean  = 2,
  eta_sd    = 0.8,
  # markup
  markup_mean = 2,
  markup_sd   = 0.4,
  # gamma
  gamma_mean = 0.5,
  gamma_sd   = 0.2
)

Parameters <- c(Parms,unc_parms)

draw_eta <- function() {
  mu     <- parms[['eta_mean']] 
  sigma  <- parms[['eta_sd']] 
  return(rnorm(1, mu, sigma))
}

draw_markup <- function() {
  mu     <- parms[['markup_mean']] 
  sigma  <- parms[['markup_sd']] 
  return(rnorm(1, mu, sigma))
}

draw_gamma <- function() {
  mu     <- parms[['gamma_mean']]
  sigma  <- parms[['gamma_sd']]
  return(rnorm(1, mu, sigma))
}

#==============================================================================
## Draw a simulation
draw_simulation <- function(time, init_state, parms, options, montecarlo, iter_num) {
  
  # Drawing of the parameters
  parms['eta_p']  <-  draw_eta()
  parms['markup'] <-  draw_markup()
  parms['gamma']  <-  draw_gamma()
  
  # Run of a simulation
  Draw_simu <- try(simulation(time       = time,
                          init_state = init_state, 
                          parms       = parms, 
                          options    = options,
                          montecarlo = T))
  
  # Return
  return(list(draw = c(parms['eta_p'], parms['markup'], parms['gamma']), 
              sim = Draw_simu))
}

## Process several iterations of drawings
data_simulations <- function(iter             = 10,
                             time             = Time,
                             init_state       = IC, 
                             parms            = Parameters, 
                             options          = Options,
                             montecarlo       = T) {
  
  # Begin of calculation
  start_time  <- proc.time()
  
  # Start parallel computing
  mc.cores <- getOption("mc.cores", max(1, detectCores()-1))
  cl <- makeCluster(mc.cores)
  registerDoParallel(cl)
  
  # Computation
  data <- foreach(k=1:iter, .packages='deSolve',
                  .export = functions, .combine='cbind') %dopar% {
                    drawing <- draw_simulation(time        = time,
                                               init_state    = init_state, 
                                               parms       = parms, 
                                               options    = options,
                                               montecarlo = montecarlo,
                                               iter_num = k)
                    
                    return(list(c(draw = drawing$draw, sim = drawing$sim)))
                  }
  
  # Start parallel computing
  stopCluster(cl)
  
  # End of calculation
  beep()
  end_time <- proc.time() - start_time
  print(end_time)
  
  # Returning
  return(data)
}

## Return some statistics about processed data
# Statistics
data_mean <- function(iter, data, time, parms) {
  
  ## Time
  year    <- data[[1]]$year
  
  ## Extraction of data
  
  # Initialize
  data_lambda    <- list(data[[1]]$lambda)
  data_omega     <- list(data[[1]]$omega)
  data_pi        <- list(data[[1]]$pi)
  
  data_gp        <- list(diff(log(data[[1]]$p), lag = (1/time['step']))*100)
  
  data_d         <- list(data[[1]]$d)
  data_p         <- list(data[[1]]$p)
  
  # Extract
  for (k in 2:iter) {
    data_lambda     <- c(data_lambda,list(data[[k]]$lambda))
    data_omega      <- c(data_omega,list(data[[k]]$omega))
    data_pi         <- c(data_pi,list(data[[k]]$pi))
    
    data_gp         <- c(data_gp,list(diff(log(data[[k]]$p), lag = (1/time['step']))*100))
    
    data_d     <- c(data_d,list(data[[k]]$d))
    
    data_p     <- c(data_p,list(data[[k]]$p))
  }
  
  ## Operators
  
  # Mean
  mean    <- function(iter,data) {
    mean    <- rep(0,length(data[[1]]))
    for (k in 1:iter) {
      mean  <- mean + data[[k]]/iter
    }
    return(mean)
  }
  
  ## Computation
  mean_lambda    <- mean(iter = iter, data = data_lambda)
  mean_omega     <- mean(iter = iter, data = data_omega)
  mean_pi        <- mean(iter = iter, data = data_pi)
  mean_gp        <- mean(iter = iter, data = data_gp)
  mean_d         <- mean(iter = iter, data = data_d)
  mean_p         <- mean(iter = iter, data = data_p)

  
  ## Graphics
  par(mfrow = c(2,2), mar=c(3.1, 4.1, 4.1, 5.1), xpd=TRUE)
  
  plot(x = year, y = mean_lambda, type = 'l', col = 'blue', xlab = '', ylab = '', ylim = c(0,1))
  lines(x = year, y = mean_omega, type = 'l', col = 'royalblue')
  lines(x = year, y = mean_pi, type = 'l', col = 'purple')
  lines(x = year, y = mean_n, type = 'l', col = 'magenta')
  lines(x = year, y = mean_Dam, type = 'l', col = 'red')
  lines(x = year, y = (mean_div/(mean_p*mean_Y)), type = 'l', col = 'orange')
  legend("right", inset=c(-.25,0), legend = c(expression(lambda), expression(omega), expression(pi), "n", "Dam", "div"), title = "Ratios", col=c("blue", "royalblue", "purple", "magenta", "red", "orange"), lty=1:1, box.lty=0, cex=0.75)
  
  plot(x = year[(1/time['step']+1):length(year)], y = mean_gY, xlab = '', ylab = '', type = 'l', col ='blue', ylim = c(-4,6))
  lines(x = year[(1/time['step']+1):length(year)], y = mean_ga, xlab = '', ylab = '', type = 'l', col ='purple')
  lines(x = year[(1/time['step']+1):length(year)], y = mean_gN, xlab = '', ylab = '', type = 'l', col ='magenta')
  lines(x = year[(1/time['step']+1):length(year)], y = mean_gp, xlab = '', ylab = '', type = 'l', col ='red')
  legend("right", inset=c(-.25,0), legend = c("GDP", "a", "N", "p"), title = "Growths", col=c("blue", "purple", "magenta", "red"), lty=1:1, box.lty=0, cex=0.75)
  
  plot(x = year, y = mean_d, type = 'l', col = 'blue', xlab = '', ylab = '')
  legend("right", inset=c(-.2,0), legend = c("d"), col=c("blue"), lty=1:1, box.lty=0, cex=0.75)
  
  plot(x = year, y = mean_Temp, type = 'l', col = 'blue', xlab = '', ylab = '', ylim = c(0,7))
  lines(x = year, y = mean_Temp0, type = 'l', col = 'purple')
  legend("right", inset=c(-.2,0), legend = c("AT", "LO"), title = "Temp", col=c("blue", "purple"), lty=1:1, box.lty=0, cex=0.75)
  
  ## Gathering and returning
  out            <- list(
    mean_lambda = mean_lambda,
    mean_omgea  = mean_omega,
    mean_pi     = mean_pi,
    mean_gp     = mean_gp,
    mean_d      = mean_d,
    mean_p      = mean_p
  )
  
  return(out)
}

# EXAMPLE OF MONTE CARLO CODE

# Set up simulations
lambda  =  0.9 
omega   =  0.9
debt    =  0.2
IC <- c(
  lambda  =  lambda, 
  omega   =  omega,
  debt    =  debt
)

Time <- c(
  start         =     2020, 
  end           =     2070,
  step          =     0.05
)
#==============================================================================
## MONTE CARLO SIMULATION
iter <- 200
savefile <- sprintf("Code/May_2020/3d/mc_data/iter_%g_lmb_%g_omg_%g_d_%g.Rdata",
                    iter, lambda, omega, debt)
load(savefile)
#dd <- data_simulations(iter)
#bad_runs <- vapply(dd,is.character,FUN.VALUE=logical(1))
#dd <- dd[!bad_runs]
#==============================================================================
# Plots
dd1 <- map(dd, ~tibble(
  time=2020:2070, 
  lambda=.$sim.lambda,
  d=.$sim.d,
  omega = .$sim.omega,
  pi = .$sim.pi))

## combine elements into a single data frame
dd2 <- (bind_rows(dd1,.id="rep")
        ## collapse statevars to long format
        %>% gather(statevar,value,-c(rep,time))
)

ggplot(dd2, aes(time,value,group=rep))+
  geom_line(alpha=0.5)+
  facet_wrap(~statevar,scale="free")

## summarize and draw lower/upper quantiles
dd3 <- (dd2
        %>% group_by(time,statevar)
        %>% summarise(mean=mean(value),
                      lwr=quantile(value,0.025),
                      upr=quantile(value,0.975))
)

ggplot(dd3,aes(time,y=mean,ymin=lwr,ymax=upr))+
  geom_line(colour='blue') + geom_ribbon(colour=NA,alpha=0.3,fill='blue') +
  facet_wrap(~statevar,scale="free")

Computing the Partial Rank Coefficients (PRCCs)

library('sensitivity')
eta <- replicate(10,draw_eta())
markup <- replicate(10,draw_markup())
gamma <- replicate(10,draw_gamma())
X<-data_frame(eta,markup,gamma)
IC <- c(
  lambda  =  0.9, 
  omega   =  0.9,
  debt    =  0.2
)
# Set up simulation
Time <- c(
  start         =     2020, 
  end           =     2100,
  step          =     0.05
)
Options <- list(
  transform_vars  = TRUE  # T / F
)

res<- rep(0,10)
for (i in 1:10){
  Parms[['eta_p']] = eta[i]
  Parms[['markup']] = markup[i]
  Parms[['gamma']] = gamma[i]

  ## Run a scenario
  Sim <- try(simulation(time             = Time,
                         init_state       = IC,
                         parms            = Parms,
                         method           = 'lsoda'
  ))
  res[i] <- tail(Sim$lambda, 1)
}

pcc(X,res,rank=TRUE)

# Call:
# pcc(X = X, y = res, rank = TRUE)
# 
# Partial Rank Correlation Coefficients (PRCC):
#            original
# eta     0.542403438
# markup  0.989757619
# gamma  -0.006482916
IC <- c(
  lambda  =  0.7, 
  omega   =  0.75,
  debt    =  0.8
)
res<- rep(0,10)
for (i in 1:10){
  Parms[['eta_p']] = eta[i]
  Parms[['markup']] = markup[i]
  Parms[['gamma']] = gamma[i]

  ## Run a scenario
  Sim <- try(simulation(time             = Time,
                         init_state       = IC,
                         parms            = Parms,
                         method           = 'lsoda'
  ))
  res[i] <- tail(Sim$lambda, 1)
}

pcc(X,res,rank=TRUE)

# Call:
# pcc(X = X, y = res, rank = TRUE)
# 
# Partial Rank Correlation Coefficients (PRCC):
#            original
# eta     0.542403438
# markup  0.989757619
# gamma  -0.006482916

I still need to read more about PRCCs. However, from S. M. Blower et al. (1991), “The magnitude of the PRCC indicates the importance of the uncertainty in estimating the value of the specific variable in contributing to the prediction imprecision.”
